# Web architecture constraints

- `web` consumes `api-gateway`, never `datalake` directly.
- Keep `datalake` as the source of truth for canonical platform data.
- Keep service boundaries explicit: `datalake`, `mcp-stocklake`, `api-gateway`, `analytics`, `screener`.
- Treat `mcp-stocklake` as the OpenClaw-facing tool service.
- Keep `api-gateway` as the public SaaS-facing API boundary.
- Keep `analytics` and `screener` as separate derived-data services.
- Keep business logic in service layers, not route handlers.
- Require MCP tools to wrap existing service-layer methods.
- OpenClaw skills must provide concise tool-use guidance only.
- Keep TimescaleDB migration concerns localized to storage layers and migrations.
- Test coverage is mandatory at unit, integration, and E2E levels.
